│ non-instruction scalars (like function arguments/constants) to a dominating location. In the                    │
│ CreateInsertElement lambda, I will guard the builder insertion point and, when the scalar is not an             │
│ Instruction, temporarily set the insertion point to the start of the function’s entry block (which dominates    │
│ all blocks) before emitting the insertelement, then restore the original insertion point. This ensures          │
│ dominance without affecting cases where the scalar depends on an instruction (handled by existing postponement  │
│ logic).                                                                                                         │
