│ THOUGHT: The crash happens because a shufflevector is emitted in a block that is not dominated by the           │
│ insertelement which builds the pointer vector operand. A minimal and robust fix is to ensure that when we       │
│ insert a non-instruction pointer scalar into a vector (CreateInsertElement), we emit that insertelement at a    │
│ dominating location. I will modify the CreateInsertElement lambda to temporarily set the builder insertion      │
│ point to the function entry block after allocas for pointer-typed, non-instruction scalars before creating the  │
│ insertelement. Then I will verify the reproducer and submit the patch.                                          │
│                                                                                                                 │
│ ```bash                                                                                                         │
│ python3 - << 'PY' && /llvm-autofix/build/llvm-build/128770/bin/opt -S --passes=slp-vectorizer                   │
│ -mtriple=x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu -mcpu=skylake /tmp/test.ll >/dev/null && submit-patch                         │
│ from pathlib import Path                                                                                        │
│ p = Path("llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp")                                                     │
