│ THOUGHT: The crash occurs because a shufflevector is emitted before an insertelement operand defined later in   │
│ the same basic block, violating dominance. A minimal, low-risk fix is to move such insertelement operands to    │
│ just before the current IRBuilder insertion point at the time of emitting the shuffle. This preserves ordering  │
│ across blocks and avoids hoisting/cloning that previously broke tests. I will inject an intra-block dominance   │
│ fix into both ShuffleIRBuilder::createShuffleVector overloads, moving any same-block insertelement operands     │
│ before the shuffle’s insertion point.                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                 │
│ ```bash                                                                                                         │
│ python3 - << 'PY' && submit-patch                                                                               │
│ from pathlib import Path, re                                                                                    │
