│ the beginning of the current insertion block (after any PHIs/allocas), so it dominates any subsequent shuffles  │
│ emitted in that block. This avoids broad reordering across blocks and preserves test expectations that are      │
│ sensitive to early allocas.                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                 │
│ ```bash                                                                                                         │
│ python3 - << 'PY' && submit-patch                                                                               │
│ from pathlib import Path, re                                                                                    │
│ p = Path("llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp")                                                     │
│ s = p.read_text()                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                 │
│ # Insert a guarded insertion-point adjustment in CreateInsertElement for pointer/non-instruction scalars.       │
│ pat = r'(Vec = Builder\.CreateInsertElement\(Vec, Scalar, Builder\.getInt32\(Pos\)\);\s*\n\s*InsElt =           │
